main event: An ex-pilot reported a circular, white object on approach at 1752 MST, seen for approximately 24 seconds at Olmstead AFB, PA.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 24 seconds and was observed by two reliable witnesses.
The object was described as circular in shape and was seen on approach with a steady flight.
The report mentions the location of the 'DCE' as unknown.
The document lists multiple possible conclusions, including 'possibly balloon,' 'possibly aircraft,' 'probably not,' and 'insufficient data for evaluation.'
There is a mention of a 13-foot diameter circular object with rocket steam visible and temporarily high temperature.
